==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Stagnation
<hw>Stag*na"tion</hw> <pr>(-n⟦amac⟧"sh⟦ucr⟧n)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[Cf. F. <ets>stagnation</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The
condition of being stagnant; cessation of flowing or circulation, as of
a fluid; the state of being motionless; <as>as, the <ex>stagnation</ex>
of the blood; the <ex>stagnation</ex> of water or air; the
<ex>stagnation</ex> of vapors</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The cessation of action, or of brisk action; the
state of being dull; <as>as, the <ex>stagnation</ex> of
business</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Stagworm</ent>⟦br⟧
